      "description": "This panel shows the 95th percentile execution time for Kyverno policy rules. Think of it like this: if you had 100 policy executions, 95 of them would complete within this time or faster, and only 5 would take longer.\n\nHow this works with examples:\n• Instead of showing average time (which can be misleading), this shows realistic \"worst case\" performance\n• Example: If average is 5ms but 95th percentile is 50ms, it means most executions are fast but some take much longer\n• Groups results by specific policy and rule names so you can see exactly which rules are slowest\n• Shows time in milliseconds (1000ms = 1 second) for easy reading\n\nReal-world example:\n• Policy \"disallow-privileged-containers\" rule \"check-privileged\" shows 15ms\n• This means: 95% of the time when someone tries to create a privileged container, Kyverno blocks it within 15ms\n• Only 5% of attempts take longer than 15ms to process\n\nWhy this matters more than averages:\n• Average of 10 fast (1ms) + 1 slow (100ms) executions = 10ms average (looks good!)\n• But 95th percentile would show 100ms (reveals the real problem!)\n• Helps you find which specific policies need performance tuning\n\nPerformance guide:\n• < 20ms: Your users won't notice any delay\n• 20-50ms: Slight delay but acceptable  \n• > 50ms: Users may experience noticeable slowness",
